# Step 3 — Autoload split + death RPC + kill confirm (C7 + C6 + H10)
#
# C7: client-only autoloads (Settings, ProcAudio, ServerDiscovery, and
#     the client half of StatsStore) skip their _ready work when the
#     process was launched with --server. Stops the dedicated server
#     from quietly mutating user://settings.cfg / firing HTTPRequest /
#     spawning AudioStreamGenerators. Detection lives in NetProtocol so
#     it's available before any other autoload runs.
# C6: real server_player_died RPC + client handler. Death is now an
#     explicit broadcast (victim, killer, weapon, headshot) instead of
#     being inferred client-side from new_hp<=0 in the damage RPC. The
#     killer attribution is preserved (was lost in the old _die() back-
#     door), and the death path is single-sourced.
# H10: when the killer peer equals the local player, the death handler
#      shows the kill-confirm HUD — previously only fired in practice.
#
# Tests: 22/22 pass.
#
